Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs) about the University of Warmia and Mazury

What programs are offered at the University of Warmia and Mazury?

The University of Warmia and Mazury offers over 70 fields of study across 17 faculties, including programs in engineering, medicine, environmental science, social sciences, humanities, and the arts.

Where is the University of Warmia and Mazury located?

The University of Warmia and Mazury is located in Olsztyn, in the Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship of Poland. The area is known for its beautiful lakes and forests, providing a serene environment for students.

Are there any programs taught in English at the University of Warmia and Mazury?

Yes, the University of Warmia and Mazury offers several programs taught in English, making it accessible to international students who are not proficient in Polish.
